You're missing the `BindingContext`. The page doesn't know which object to bind against. Set it in your code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

Also ensure your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or uses `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

**Common causes of blank labels:**
1. **No `BindingContext` set** ← most likely your issue
2. Property names don't match the `{Binding ...}` paths
3. Properties are fields instead of public properties
4. `INotifyPropertyChanged` not raised when values change after construction
